The National Education, Health and Allied Workers Union (NEHAWU) and National Parliament have reached an agreement on salary increases for its employees for the 2017/18 financial year.The 7.5% salary increase will take effect retrospectively from 1 April 2017 and will cover all employees in the bargaining unit.Workers had previously accused parliament of diverting money from workers to other projects, including the new Parliamentary protection services.Workers also wanted performance bonuses to be based on annual and not monthly salaries.-TNA Reporter